column521: This has been a totally crazy year due to our building project and switching to CWMARS. We moved and were closed for 5 weeks during July and August so there was no circulation and no programming. When we reopened August 6, we were on CWMARS and we did not carry over our patron database, everyone was entered into the system as they came into the library. Two thirds of our collection went into storage and is unavailable for borrowing. Between this fact and the way CWMARS operates our browsing collection was pretty much nil. As soon as new books arrived, they immediately went into the system ques leaving very few new items for browsing. Yet the staff tells me that they have been busier than ever and I see long lines at the circulation desk, but the circulation is cut in half. Since I am not familiar with the CWMARS software and how it calculates statistics, I do not know if our books being checked out at other libraries gives us the credit or if it goes to the other library. In a

column521: I believe that our number of non-resident registered users has increased as it has since there are several families who now choice their children into Bernardston Elementary School. Also, under \"Internet and Electronic Services\" you ask for the number of \"public Internet computer\" users, which sounds as though it does not include the number of patrons who access our wireless connection on their own portable computers and devices. The number of patrons using our on-site devices has decreased, but the number of patrons using their own devices with our wireless connection has increased greatly, which the number reported under \"public Internet computers\" does not reflect.

column2: West Boylston - Beaman Memorial Public Library
column521: In September 2012, we became circulating members of C/W MARS after being an Online Affiliate member since 1988. In addition, C/W MARS changed its ILS from Millenium to Evergreen. During that transistion a large number of our materials were dropped because of incomplete or missing barcodes. Some items were never entered into the database. The result is a holdings report from C/W MARS that does not accurately reflect the actual holdings of our library. After consulting with MBLC staff, we have reported last year\\\'s numbers adjusted by the number of items added and withdrawn over the course of the fiscal year. We hope to have an accurate reflection of our collection for next year\\\'s report. In addition, our Spectrum circulation numbers for July to September have been added to the numbers reported in Evergreen. I have listed the number of patrons active in Spectrum until next year.
